# 5) Channel capability matrix

## Voice - allowed actions

### Green

* employee callout reporting
* manager asking for schedule summary
* manager asking who is unfilled
* simple fill approvals when one pending action exists

### Yellow

* create a single shift when date/time/location/role resolve cleanly
* remove one worker from one shift
* open one specific shift
* publish current draft when a single publishable draft exists

### Red

* bulk rewrites
* multi-location changes
* roster changes
* template changes
* anything that benefits from visual diff review

## SMS - allowed actions

### Green

* publish schedule
* review schedule
* copy last week
* get summary
* get unfilled shifts
* open a shift
* approve or deny a pending fill

### Yellow

* create a simple shift
* remove a worker from a shift
* move one shift
* start coverage for a specific shift when multiple candidates exist

### Red

* bulk roster changes
* broad schedule rewrites
* settings or policy changes
* destructive multi-entity operations without preview

## Web AI prompt - allowed actions

### Green

* most single-entity schedule and shift edits
* conflict explanations
* draft generation
* filter/summarize issues
* approve recommended fixes

### Yellow

* multi-step schedule rewrites
* multi-shift reassignment
* high-blast-radius changes with diff preview

### Red

* auth, billing, security, or organization-wide destructive operations

