# 14) SMS product changes

## Product posture

SMS becomes a true manager action surface, but it remains narrower than the web prompt.

## Example supported requests

* "Publish next week for Studio City."
* "Open the Friday closer."
* "Who is still unfilled tomorrow?"
* "Create a host shift tomorrow 5 to 10."

## SMS rules

* prefer one-shot actions
* require explicit confirmation for yellow actions
* redirect red actions to web
* include deep links when visual review helps

## Implementation note

The current webhook already supports structured commands.

The AI-native layer should not rip those out immediately.

Recommended behavior:

* keep current explicit commands
* route non-command natural language into the AI action system
* progressively unify hard-coded commands onto the same underlying action executor later

